// 25-imports — multi-file Aperio project under the F.19 per-
// directory seed model.
//
// Three files in this directory:
//   - types.ap       — `type Trade` definition
//   - notional.ap    — `fn notional(Trade) -> Decimal` helper
//   - main.ap        — this file, with `fn main()` driving it
//
// F.19 (shipped 2026-05-11) collapses the old per-file `import`
// shape: every `.ap` file in the directory is part of one seed,
// every top-level decl is visible to every other file in the
// same directory in one shared scope. Same shape Go gets from
// per-package visibility. Build via `aperio build examples/
// 25-imports` (directory target); the binary lands at
// `examples/25-imports/25-imports`. Cross-seed imports (one
// directory reaching into another) are still deferred.
//
// Per The Design / Aperio, multi-file projects are organisational
// — the framework's coordination primitives don't change shape
// because a type lives in a sibling file. The bus and the
// region allocator stay one unit; what's different is just
// where the source TEXT lives.

fn main() {
    let t = Trade { symbol: "GOOG", price: 170.5d, qty: 100.0d };
    println(t.symbol, " notional = ", notional(t));
}
